 //////////////////////////////////README////////////////////////////////////
////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

The STATIC folder contains image, CSS and JavaScript files.

Please, note that the Cytoscape functionalities are not implemented in the current version.

Libraries used :
	- Bootstrap is used to make the site responsive
	- Cytoscape is used to generate a graph of the inferred interaction network
	- D3 is a feature-viewer dependency
	- Datatables allows us to generate modular tables
	- Feature-Viewer lets you visualize the sequence of queried proteins
	- Fonts generates icons for the site
	- JQuery injects code into html pages (used to populate results tables). JQuery is a Feature-Viewer dependency
	  
Files to be created by the developer :
	- css/style.css: contains the entire site layout (style sheet)
	- cytoscape/cytoscape.css: generates the cytoscape DIV in small or large format
	  (for result.html and cytoscape.html respectively)
	- cytoscape/network.js: generates the graph
	- dataTables/make_tables.js : defines DataTables format
	- feature-viewer/create-features.js : defines visualization tool features
	- feature-viewer/show_domains.js: fills the domains/patterns table and the 
	  sequences
	- js/options.js: resets form parameters
	- js/tooltip: generates tooltips
